title: Car.SOS.Season.1
description:
Brits have always had a love affair with cars, but when life gets in the way, sometimes things can get a little rusty. 

This is where the Car S.O.S team step in. 

Join the parts-blagging-petrol-head Tim Shaw (Fifth Gear) and master mechanic/musician Fuzz Townshend, as they join forces to rescue rusty classics from their garage prisons. 

With some grease, graft, mechanical expertise and just a little tender loving care the Car S.O.Steam rescue BritainÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s much loved classics and transform them inside and out. 

In goes a dusty, tarnished mess and out comes a swanky, shiny new auto-mobile in all its former glory, then itÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s time to hand the keys back to the shocked owner.


EPISODE GUIDE
-------------

Episode 1: Cosworth In Crisis
The Ford Cosworth was once seen as a classy car, but for Darren it's a reminder of a family tragedy. Can the guys restore it to its former glory?


Episode 2: Beetle Mania
Ã¢â‚¬ËœBorisÃ¢â‚¬â„¢ the VW Beetle may once have been a beauty but it soon found itself gathering rust in the garage. The guys attempt to restore it.

Episode 3: Phoenix Jeep
Having survived World War II, Dick Masters' Jeep was damaged in an arson attack. The guys embark on a rapid renovation project to surprise him.

Episode 4: Fiat Fiasco
Jeremy lost his wife and was unable to work after a car accident. Can the guys end his bad luck and give his Fiat Spider the makover it deserves?

Episode 5: Anglia Angels
The Hutchings-Clarke family all drive Ford Anglias, except James, whose own model doesn't even have an engine. Will the guys manage to rescue it?

Episode 6: The Rover's Return
Rover-lover SteveÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s health issues have ended his dreams of renovating his 1972 P6. Can the guys beat the odds and save Steve's beloved car?

Episode 7: Triumph Of The Stag
Tim and Fuzz head to Portsmouth on a mission to rescue an ex-navy diver's Triumph Stag and hopefully put a smile back on his face.

Episode 8: Austin Re-Powered
Tim and Fuzz travel the country searching for cars that have seen better days, and owners who need a helping hand restoring them.

Episode 9: Zodiac Come Back
The guys head to Norfolk to revive an ageing Ford Zodiac. But tensions soon arise when Fuzz changes the paint back to the original colour scheme.

Episode 10: Lotus Flowers
